post.description:
Validates up to 50 Apple MDM declaration payloads against the catalog schema and returns a result per declaration.

**Request body:**
The body contains a `declarations` array. Each item in the array is a declaration object with the following structure:
- `DeclarationType` *(string, required)* — the Apple declaration type identifier, e.g. `com.apple.configuration.network.dns-settings`.
- All other keys are the declaration payload fields specific to that type (e.g. `VisibleName`, `DNSSettings`).

**Example request:**
```json
{
"declarations": [
{
"DeclarationType": "com.apple.configuration.network.dns-settings",
"VisibleName": "My DNS",
"DNSSettings": { "DNSProtocol": "HTTPS", "ServerURL": "https://dns.example.com" }
}
]
}
```

**Response:** each result includes `declarationType`, `status` (`valid` or `invalid`), and a `reasons` array listing each validation failure with the failing `keyName` and a `message`.
